      'Malala Yousafzai is a Pakistani activist for female education and the youngest-ever Nobel Prize laureate. She is known for her advocacy of education for girls in her native Swat Valley in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, northwest Pakistan, where the local Taliban had at times banned girls from attending school. Malala starts her day with meditation and reflection. She believes in the power of education to bring positive change to the world and spends time planning and working on projects to empower girls through education. Malala is actively involved in her foundation, the Malala Fund. Her work includes advocating for policies that support girls’ education globally, working closely with world leaders, and addressing international audiences. In the evening, Malala spends time reading books and staying informed about global issues. She values family time and often engages in conversations with her family about the day’s events.',
